					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">This looks like little more than a zipped Pasofami format, except using UNIF-style board names. Personally, I'm against it, since it would <strong>require</strong> implementing ZIP support in order to even load them, and it does not provide any advantage whatsoever over UNIF (in fact, it would be arguably <em>worse</em>, since zipped UNIF would compress better anyways).</div>

					
